devdoc.details: SLA is a service level agreement contract used for service downtime compensation
SLA is a service level agreement contract used for service downtime compensation

params._hash: the ipfs hash that stores additional info
params._timestamp: the time the SLI has been registered

params._SLONames: the names of the service level objectives in a bytes32 array
params._SLOs: an array with the service level objective addresses
params._ipfsHash: the ipfs hash that stores extra information about the agreement
params._owner: the owner of the service level agreement
params._stake: the amount required to stake when subscribing to the agreement

params._SLOName: the name of the SLO in bytes32

params._periodId: the id of the given period
params._value: the value of the SLI to check
